history.content:
Here: http://classes.berkeley.edu/content/2018-fall-compsci-189-001-lec-001

it shows there are 326 enrolled with a capacity of 245, at -81 total open seats. Does this simply mean that the class was expanded from 245 to 326? It shouldn't have any effect on people that were already on the waitlist (<15) prior to the "expansion", right?

Also (adding to original poster) it seems like waitlist position didn't budge despite the expansion. Does that mean students who enrolled in Phase II had priority over students on the waitlist?
history.subject: Negative Enrollment? (CS 189)
